9. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":28,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Joan DeBeckering was born in 1354, in Lincolnshire, England. She had at least 1 son with Sir John de Bekering. She died in 1387, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1354–1387":"1354–1387","1338–1376":"1338–1376","–1386":"–1386","1338":"1338","5 October 1376":"5. oktoober 1376","1354":"1354","1387":"1387","1376":"1376","1386":"1386","1382":"1382","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1354–1387":"1354–1387","1338–1376":"1338–1376","–1386":"–1386","1338":"1338","5 October 1376":"5. lokakuuta 1376","1354":"1354","1387":"1387","1376":"1376","1386":"1386","1382":"1382","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"1354–1387":"1354–1387","1338–1376":"1338–1376","–1386":"–1386","1338":"1338","5 October 1376":"5 octobre 1376","1354":"1354","1387":"1387","1376":"1376","1386":"1386","1382":"1382","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre